<p>September 7, 2016<br /><strong>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</strong><br />
  Contact: PACER Center 952-838-9000, 800-53-PACER</p>
<h2>PACER CENTER TO HOST FAMILY FUN DAY AND TECH EXPO SEPT. 17</h2>


<h4>Free event for families of children and young adults with disabilities</h4>
<p>Children and young adults with disabilities, their families, and the professionals who serve them can discover the latest in assistive technology (AT), and enjoy hands-on fun during the Simon Technology Center&rsquo;s Family Fun Day and Tech Expo. It will be on Saturday, Sept. 17, from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m., at PACER Center, 8161 Normandale Blvd., in Bloomington, Minn. Advance registration is required.</p>
<p>Participants can touch, see, and try a variety of assistive technology that supports play, learning, work and more. They will be able to test drive a robot, visit the do-it-yourself technology station, view iPad app demonstrations, and much more. The activities are appropriate for all ages.</p>
<p>To register, go to pacer.org/workshops or call PACER at (952) 838-9000. In Greater Minnesota, call (800) 537-2237 (toll free) or visit PACER.org.</p>
